comment:
* A class that represents a DNS lookup event initiated through the standard network stack. * *

It contains information about the originating app as well as the DNS hostname and resolved * IP addresses.

variables.name: mHostname
variables.comment: The hostname that was looked up.

variables.name: mIpAddresses
variables.comment: Contains (possibly a subset of) the IP addresses returned.

variables.name: mIpAddressesCount
variables.comment:
* The number of IP addresses returned from the DNS lookup event. May be different from the
     * length of ipAddresses if there were too many addresses to log.

methods.name: public String getHostname()
methods.comment: Returns the hostname that was looked up.

methods.name: public List<InetAddress> getInetAddresses()
methods.comment: Returns (possibly a subset of) the IP addresses returned.

methods.name: public int getTotalResolvedAddressCount()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of IP addresses returned from the DNS lookup event. May be different from
     * the length of the list returned by {@link #getInetAddresses()} if there were too many
     * addresses to log.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
